<TITLE> Three shot in old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 03 (bdnews24.com)--Three men on Thursday were shot and wounded by unidentified criminals in old Dhaka in two incidents in the space of half an hour, police said. Officer in charge of Sutrapur Police Station Mohammad Hanif told bdnews24.com Golap Hossain, 45, and Faruk Hossain, 30, were injured as two criminals randomly fired at them. He said criminals had demanded Tk 1 crore from Lal Mian, who owns City Fan Ltd, several days ago, but he did not oblige them and the shooting incident might have been a revenge act. Golap, who and Faruk are the car drivers of Mian, said two criminals riding a motorcycle asked them at 11am in front of Mian's home at Lalmoni Street if it was his residence. As they said 'yes', they fired and wounded them in the legs. The third man injured half an hour ago was Abul Kalam Azad, manager of Akbar Steel House at North South Road in Bangshal. . He was at Akbar Steel House shop when unknown gunmen fired at him at 10:30am. Officer in charge of Bangshal Police Station told bdnews24.com that his condition is critical and added that he might have been a victim of personal enmity. bdne
